Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water
to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a garlic press).

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}.

Pop the tomatoes onto a piece of #foil{}.

Drizzle over some @olive oil{some}. Season with @salt{some}, @pepper{some} and the
@sugar{1/2%tsp}. Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel, then place onto
a small #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, roast the tomato parcel on the top shelf until softened,
~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%grams} to the boiling water and bring back
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{some} in a large #frying pan{} on
medium heat. Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and fry
until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @water for the sauce{150%ml}
and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly
reduced, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once reduced, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%grams}, bring back to the boil,
then remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{}, then add to the pan of creamy sauce
along with the @peas{120%grams} and heat through for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and
piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}, then taste and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if you feel
it needs it.

When everything's piping hot, spoon the creamy chicken pasta into your #bowls{}
and drizzle over the @pesto{32%grams}.

Carefully remove your roasted tomatoes from the foil and serve them on top.

Spoon over the tomato juices from the parcel to finish. Enjoy!